The paper focuses on formalizing extensive games, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and game theory. The use of COQ, a proof assistant, suggests a focus on logic and formal methods, which is reflected in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of dependent types, which is a topic that falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper's focus on game theory suggests a fit with the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of infiniteness in game theory suggests a fit with the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
